   "body" : "With current git master, the system tray icon disappears immediately when you tell Bitcoin-Qt to exit. It used to stay until the client shutdown completely. I see that this was intentional in pull #867, but it makes development/debugging more difficult and may cause more confusion when a user gets an error that Bitcoin-Qt is already running when he tries to restart it.\r\n\r\nHow about changing the icon, setting a \"shutting down\" tooltip, or similar instead?",
